<p>Coral reefs cover less than 1% of the ocean floor but they are among the most productive and diverse ecosystems on Earth.&nbsp;</p>
<p>reefs support 25 percent of all known marine species.<br />
“the rainforests of the sea”&nbsp;</p>
<p>Corals extract calcium carbonate from seawater to create a hard, durable exoskeleton that protects their soft, sac-like bodies</p>